<task id="019" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P1.C3 — Verify 4,844 baseline preserved after factory change</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>30-45 minutes</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-1, factory-ext, verification, bff-api, testing, p1-c, isolated</tags>
    <parallel-group>1-C-isolated</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Verification gate for the NFR-07-isolated factory edit. Same isolation envelope as task 018 — runs immediately after, before any other repair task resumes. Failure here triggers immediate revert (per design.md §6.4 binding).</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Verify that task 018's factory extension preserved the 4,844-test baseline. If the pass count
    drops below 4,844 the factory change introduced a regression and MUST be reverted before
    any other repair task resumes.

    Per design.md §6.4 binding rule: "MUST run full suite before AND after any
    `CustomWebAppFactory.cs` change."

    Per CLAUDE.md NFR-07: this task stays inside the isolation envelope opened by task 018.
    The isolation envelope closes ONLY when this task confirms baseline preserved.

    Pure measurement — NO code changes.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent confirming or failing the factory extension based on baseline preservation.</role>

  <goal>
    Either:
    - SUCCESS path: pass count ≥ 4,844 (baseline preserved); plus additional tests now reach
      the assertion phase (factory unblocked them); delta documented in
      `baseline/post-factory-delta-2026-MM-DD.txt`; isolation envelope closed; subsequent
      Phase 1 / Phase 2+3 work cleared to resume.
    - FAILURE path: pass count drops below 4,844; HALT; investigate the regression; revert task
      018 if the cause can't be addressed by adjusting the additive entries; document the
      revert in `current-task.md` and `decisions/` and re-plan task 017 inventory.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="baseline-phase-0">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx</file>
    <file purpose="baseline-post-compile">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/post-compile-delta-2026-MM-DD.txt</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No production code modifications; measurement only</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-07">Verification stays inside isolation envelope; no other repair task may execute in parallel</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md §6.4">MUST run full suite after factory change; baseline preservation is the gate</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md §4.5">If regression discovered, REVERT factory; do not patch the regression by further factory restructuring</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The factory's blast radius is wide. Task 018's additive changes COULD unintentionally
      change a test's behavior: a previously-not-present config key, once present, might wire
      up code that the test wasn't expecting to run. This verification gate is the only way to
      catch that. If the gate fails, the revert is cheap (single file); fixing-forward is
      expensive (cascading retest of every newly-touched code path).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="018" status="not-started">Factory extended additively</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/post-factory-delta-2026-MM-DD.txt</file>
    <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/post-factory-2026-MM-DD.trx</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Run full test suite: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ -c Release --logger "trx;LogFileName=post-factory-2026-MM-DD.trx" --results-directory projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/`. Allow up to 30 min runtime.</step>
    <step order="2">Parse TRX summary: extract total / passed / failed / skipped counts.</step>
    <step order="3">Compare PASS count vs Phase 0 baseline (4,844) AND vs post-compile baseline from task 014:
      - IF passed &gt;= 4,844 AND total ≥ post-compile total → SUCCESS path
      - IF passed &lt; 4,844 → FAILURE path</step>
    <step order="4">[SUCCESS path] Write `baseline/post-factory-delta-2026-MM-DD.txt` with: (a) total/passed/failed/skipped, (b) delta vs 4,844 baseline, (c) delta vs post-compile baseline (expected: more tests pass because factory unblocked them), (d) declaration "Isolation envelope CLOSED; repair tracks cleared to resume."</step>
    <step order="5">[FAILURE path] HALT all other work. Investigate: identify which previously-passing tests now fail. Determine if the new config key is the cause. Options: (a) tune the fake value (rerun 018 with adjusted entries), (b) revert the factory change entirely (`git checkout tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/CustomWebAppFactory.cs`), or (c) split task 018 into smaller increments. Document the path chosen + rationale in `decisions/D-02-factory-regression-{date}.md`.</step>
    <step order="6">Update `current-task.md` with outcome (SUCCESS or FAILURE + action taken).</step>
    <step order="7">Verify `git status` shows no source code modifications.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test (full suite + TRX logger)</tool>
    <tool name="git">status, checkout (only if revert is needed per step 5)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/post-factory-delta-2026-MM-DD.txt</output>
    <output type="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/post-factory-2026-MM-DD.trx</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">post-factory-*.trx exists and is parseable</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">post-factory-delta-*.txt exists with delta vs 4,844 + delta vs post-compile baseline</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SUCCESS path: pass count ≥ 4,844; isolation envelope closed in `current-task.md`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">FAILURE path: regression documented + decision file written; factory reverted if appropriate</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No modifications to `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No other repair task ran concurrently with 018+019 (NFR-07; verify via `current-task.md` history)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <completion-notes date="2026-05-31">
    SUCCESS path executed. Full suite re-measured: 6,034 / 5,753 / 172 / 109 — identical to task 018's
    post-edit report (zero drift across runs). Cumulative Phase 0 → Wave 1.3 reduction: 342 → 172
    failures (−170 / −49.7%). All 7 inventory keys from task 017 verified present in CustomWebAppFactory.cs.
    Zero passing-test regressions (5,753 ≥ 5,627 Wave-1.1a baseline AND ≥ 4,844 Phase 0 design baseline).
    Build clean (0 errors, 17 pre-existing warnings). NFR-07 isolation envelope CLOSED; P1.C track exit
    declared. Authoritative post-Wave-1.3 baseline written to
    `baseline/post-wave1.3-authoritative-baseline-2026-05-31.md` for Phase 2+3 to cite per §6.3.
    Outputs: post-019-verify-2026-05-31.trx + post-wave1.3-authoritative-baseline-2026-05-31.md.
  </completion-notes>
</task>
